HEADWORD: Epineurium
<hw>Ep`i*neu"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>'epi`</grk> upon + <?/ a nerve.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The connective tissue framework and sheath of a nerve which bind
together the nerve bundles, each of which has its own special sheath, or
perineurium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

